---
title: Brown Sugar Bourbon Chicken with Apple Pan Sauce, Garlic Mashed Potatoes & Zesty Green Beans
description: Winner winner chicken dinner! Chicken cutlets are satisfying, speedy, and so versatile, which is why our chefs are always thinking up new ways to take them to the next level. This week, they amped up the flavors... big time. Sweet and savory is the name of the game here. Coated in brown sugar bourbon spice, these chicken cutlets are seared and topped with a buttery apple pan sauce. Zesty green beans and garlic mashed potatoes pair perfectly with the main event. Prepare yourself for a flavor explosion.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/62163b653a110037fe2eac53-df2aadd3.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/brown-sugar-bourbon-chicken-62163b653a110037fe2eac53-4fa88d28.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 58 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 1080 mg
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/brown-sugar-bourbon-chicken-62163b653a110037fe2eac53
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Peel @Garlic{1%clove}. Place potatoes and whole garlic in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes and garlic to pot.

Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

Meanwhile, halve, core, and dice @Apple{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}, @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

While green beans roast, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season lightly with salt and pepper, then rub all over with @Brown Sugar Bourbon Seasoning{10.8%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat @Butter{2%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add apple and scallion whites; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, ½ cup water, and @Sugar{½%teaspoon}. (For 4, use ¾ cup water and 1 tsp sugar.) Cook until apple is tender and sauce has thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

In the last 2 minutes of cooking, return chicken to pan; turn a few times to coat.

While sauce cooks, mash potatoes and garlic with @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} and 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If necessary, rewarm over low heat.

Toss green beans with lemon zest.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and green beans between plates. Spoon remaining pan sauce over chicken and garnish with scallion greens. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.